142
00:14:48,910 --> 00:14:52,180
I also need you.

143
00:15:45,670 --> 00:15:48,840
What are you doing right now?

144
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:50,630
I'm sorry. I didn't know you were here.

145
00:15:50,630 --> 00:15:54,790
Have you been helping Joon Young so that this would happen?

146
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:57,720
Then, why did you help him, Grandma?

147
00:15:57,720 --> 00:16:00,040
What were you hoping for?

148
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:01,940
I wasn't hoping for anything.

149
00:16:05,940 --> 00:16:10,300
I just wanted Joon Young to happily play the piano which he loves so much.

150
00:16:11,830 --> 00:16:14,060
Then, you've failed.

151
00:16:14,060 --> 00:16:19,400
Joon Young has never once been happy playing the piano.

152
00:16:22,370 --> 00:16:24,670
Because he was burdened by the money we gave him,

153
00:16:24,670 --> 00:16:26,630
he only played because he had to. For me, you,

154
00:16:26,630 --> 00:16:29,840
and the foundation.

155
00:16:32,630 --> 00:16:35,550
But I got too used to it...

156
00:16:37,350 --> 00:16:40,000
To Joon Young's piano playing.

157
00:16:43,350 --> 00:16:48,870
The thing that comforted me wasn't you or Father.

158
00:16:48,870 --> 00:16:51,980
It was Joon Young, who played this piano.

159
00:16:54,170 --> 00:16:56,880
I don't have any talents anymore,

160
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:59,220
and I even gave Hyeon Ho up.

161
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:02,840
I can't lose Joon Young too.

162
00:17:29,820 --> 00:17:33,100
 Joon Young, I can't reach you on the phone. 

163
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:34,930
 We got the money! 

164
00:17:34,930 --> 00:17:38,160
 Your dad has it all solved, so don't worry. 

165
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:40,160
 I'm coming to Seoul. 

166
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,330
 Let's talk when I'm there. 

167
00:17:56,230 --> 00:17:59,650
