Do you think it's worth going?

262
00:26:50,830 --> 00:26:54,020
It just started not long ago...

263
00:26:54,020 --> 00:26:56,630
But Unni, you were a intern with Kyunghoo before, weren't you?

264
00:26:56,630 --> 00:26:58,050
I'm also kind of curious.

265
00:26:58,050 --> 00:27:00,670
Let's go.

266
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:09,670
Sorry, I'm late.

267
00:27:11,790 --> 00:27:16,830
Oh, right... I heard you said something to the teaching assistant about the piano in the practice room.

268
00:27:17,780 --> 00:27:21,790
The pianos at the school are pretty lousy, aren't they?

269
00:27:21,790 --> 00:27:24,880
If there's nowhere for you to practice, you can practice here if you want.

270
00:27:26,950 --> 00:27:29,290
All right!

271
00:27:32,390 --> 00:27:36,300
   

272
00:27:40,390 --> 00:27:44,150
To summarize what I talked about,

273
00:27:44,150 --> 00:27:46,950
the performance ability of a classical performer is essential.

274
00:27:46,950 --> 00:27:50,070
As well as the ability to self-market and plan

275
00:27:50,070 --> 00:27:54,350
is not merely needed, but mandatory.

276
00:27:54,350 --> 00:27:58,170
I'll end my talk here today.

277
00:27:58,170 --> 00:28:00,330
Thank you for listening.

278
00:28:00,330 --> 00:28:04,470
All right, so far, we've heard great words

279
00:28:04,470 --> 00:28:06,930
from Kyunghoo Foundation's Chairman Na Moon Sook

280
00:28:06,930 --> 00:28:09,000
and Marketing Team Leader Cha Young In.

281
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:11,030
Are you going to continue being like this?

282
00:28:11,980 --> 00:28:15,270
How many times have I told you this isn't correct?

283
00:28:17,350 --> 00:28:20,630
Are you going to continue playing however you want to like this?

284
00:28:23,040 --> 00:28:25,720
Is that wrong?

285
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:28,680
What did you say?

286
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:34,580
Am I not even allowed to play the piano however I want?

287
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:49,890
You said you wanted to get first place.

288
00:28:51,010 --> 00:28:53,830
If you want to play how you want and win first place too,

289
00:28:53,830 --> 00:28:55,580
you must first have such overwhelming talent

290
00:28:55,580 --> 00:28:59,610
so no one can touch you like Seung Ji Min or Kim Gyu Hee!

291
00:29:01,010 --> 00:29:03,370
But you're not them.

292
00:29:03,370 --> 00:29:05,520
Don't you get what I'm saying?

293
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:13,690
Let's stop here today.

294
00:29:13,690 --> 00:29:15,570
Rest for a day.

295
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:26,990
I'm a flute major. I'm also interested in performance planning.

296
00:29:26,990 --> 00:29:31,170
But looking at the people around me who graduated from music school and worked in performance,

297
00:29:31,170 --> 00:29:35,220
oddly, a lot of people quit really quickly.

298
00:29:35,220 --> 00:29:39,230
Is there some particular reason for that?

299
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:45,430
For those who start playing music and transition to planning,

300
00:29:45,430 --> 00:29:47,590
and I'm being careful to say this,

301
00:29:47,590 --> 00:29:50,720
they weren't able to handle their own emotions,

302
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:53,890
and in many cases give up.

303
00:29:53,890 --> 00:29:58,270
They wear dark clothes to not stand out, and they wait behind a darkened stage.

304
00:29:58,270 --> 00:30:01,910
and for the sake of those colleagues who studied music with them,

305
00:30:01,910 --> 00:30:06,610
they now quietly watch them receive the spotlight and play music.

306
00:30:06,610 --> 00:30:09,750
I think that thought is what's hard for them.

307
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:13,900
To give up such a fervent dream,

308
00:30:13,900 --> 00:30:17,750
is easier said than done.

309
00:30:23,100 --> 00:30:24,550
Team Leader!

310
00:30:24,550 --> 00:30:25,890
Oh, you're here!

311
00:30:25,890 --> 00:30:30,270
Of course, I had to come! I really enjoyed the talk today!

312
00:30:30,270 --> 00:30:32,650
Song Ah! Come over here.

313
00:30:32,650 --> 00:30:34,540
Song Ah, you're here.

314
00:30:34,540 --> 00:30:35,570
How have you been?

315
00:30:35,570 --> 00:30:37,200
Song Ah!

316
00:30:38,090 --> 00:30:41,350
- Our summer interns, right?
 - Yes.

317
00:30:42,750 --> 00:30:49,000
Oh right! I remembered last time you complimented how hard a worker Song Ah was

318
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:54,300
so while I was getting my chamber together I had her do my secretarial work.

319
00:30:54,300 --> 00:30:55,940
Ah, I see...

320
00:30:55,940 --> 00:31:00,150
 She's such a hard and diligent worker! 

321
00:31:00,150 --> 00:31:04,410
Not just you, but Joon Young also is such a good judge of character!

322
00:31:04,410 --> 00:31:09,180
You couldn't ask for a better wife for a performer.

323
00:31:10,970 --> 00:31:14,920
- I'm sorry? 
 - Well, nowadays women all have their own job keeping them busy,

324
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:17,910
but honestly, for musicians like Joon Young who go on tour,

325
00:31:17,910 --> 00:31:21,960
they need a wife who packs their bags and manages their schedule, after all.

326
00:31:21,960 --> 00:31:24,050
That's not a bad thing.

327
00:31:24,050 --> 00:31:27,150
That's how they can focus on their music only, without having to worry

328
00:31:27,150 --> 00:31:29,050
about bothersome things like managing their money.

329
00:31:29,050 --> 00:31:31,890
- Excuse me— 
 - Joon Young

330
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:35,910
isn't one to date someone over that kind of thing.

331
00:31:38,690 --> 00:31:41,670
Ah, yes. Of course, Director Na.

332
00:31:41,670 --> 00:31:46,620
I was just saying it because I find it so adorable that they are dating.

333
00:31:46,620 --> 00:31:48,950
Yes, of course, you were.

334
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:03,450
- Yes. 
 - That's right.

335
00:32:03,450 --> 00:32:07,110
- Well then, be safe on your way. 
 - Yes.

336
00:32:07,110 --> 00:32:09,240
- I'll see you some other time. 
 - Goodbye.

337
00:32:09,240 --> 00:32:11,380
- Thank you for your work. 
 - Yes.

338
00:32:12,710 --> 00:32:13,970
Joon Young!

339
00:32:13,970 --> 00:32:15,360
Oh, Master Park Joon Young!

340
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:18,040
- You're here? 
 - Hello, Oppa.

341
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:20,220
Hello.

342
00:32:30,230 --> 00:32:38,260
All this time... I've been hurting many people.

343
00:32:38,260 --> 00:32:42,730
The closer they were, the more they have been hurt.

344
00:32:46,550 --> 00:32:53,110
Joon Young. Chairman Lee, Jung Kyung's Dad.

345
00:32:53,110 --> 00:32:56,850
Even keeping his own position is too much for him.

346
00:32:58,080 --> 00:33:00,760
He is too soft.

347
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:09,610
I thought I needed someone to protect the foundation after my passing.

348
00:33:10,810 --> 00:33:16,500
That's why when it came to who would be next to Jung Kyung, rather than picking who she wanted,

349
00:33:16,500 --> 00:33:21,830
I preferred someone who would want to be the son-in-law for Kyunghoo Group,

350
00:33:21,830 --> 00:33:28,110
someone who would want to be the board director of the foundation. That's what I thought.

351
00:33:30,930 --> 00:33:33,450
I was only worried about myself,

352
00:33:34,810 --> 00:33:38,490
I couldn't see into your heart.

353
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:44,150
I am sorry.

354
00:33:49,070 --> 00:33:51,110
Please don't be.

355
00:33:52,620 --> 00:33:59,400
I realized too late what you meant to Jung Kyung.

356
00:34:03,890 --> 00:34:09,860
Joon Young, could you stay by Jung Kyung's side?

357
00:34:18,030 --> 00:34:20,190
My apologies.

358
00:34:21,980 --> 00:34:28,550
I have... no such feelings anymore.

359
00:34:31,990 --> 00:34:33,380
I see.

360
00:34:33,380 --> 00:34:36,440
I realized that too late as well.

361
00:34:42,020 --> 00:34:44,050
I'm sorry.

362
00:34:56,250 --> 00:35:01,760
People really... say whatever they please.

363
00:35:03,390 --> 00:35:07,470
Not everybody is an adult just because they are older.

364
00:35:12,300 --> 00:35:16,030
But still, I'm envious.

365
00:35:16,030 --> 00:35:19,680
What? Of what?

366
00:35:20,580 --> 00:35:24,860
People who say everything they want.

367
00:35:24,860 --> 00:35:27,130
I envy them.

368
00:35:27,130 --> 00:35:31,620
Even though they hurt other people by doing that?

369
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:41,910
Still, at least they can protect themselves.

370
00:35:42,630 --> 00:35:46,450
So that other people can't hurt them however they please.

371
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:03,890
You don't have to walk me out, it's fine.

372
00:36:03,890 --> 00:36:05,960
Still, I can accompany you to where your driver—

373
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:09,120
No, I'm really fine.

374
00:36:12,480 --> 00:36:18,870
Brahms. I think I can listen to you playing Brahms now, no?

375
00:36:21,230 --> 00:36:27,370
I really want to hear it one day. Can you grant me that favor?

376
00:36:30,410 --> 00:36:32,020
Yes.

377
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:38,730
Thank you, Joon Young.

378
00:36:39,700 --> 00:36:43,310
Be well. Take care.

379
00:37:22,290 --> 00:37:26,150
Did your meeting with Director Na go well?

380
00:37:27,500 --> 00:37:29,320
Yes.

381
00:37:32,710 --> 00:37:37,490
What about you? Did it go well with Young In Noona?

382
00:37:38,550 --> 00:37:40,270
Yes.

383
00:37:46,640 --> 00:37:49,660
I'll go see Jung Kyung.

384
00:37:51,120 --> 00:37:53,860
To return the sheet music of the accompaniment to her.

385
00:37:58,550 --> 00:38:03,870
Today will be the last time. Seeing Jung Kyung, that is.

386
00:38:21,630 --> 00:38:23,710
It's really great.

387
00:38:23,710 --> 00:38:26,990
The sound seems firmer and the reverberation is good.

388
00:38:26,990 --> 00:38:28,430
You did something to the sound post, didn't you?

389
00:38:28,430 --> 00:38:32,530
Yes. I'm glad you like it.

390
00:38:32,530 --> 00:38:34,920
Woah, instruments are fascinating.

391
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:38,670
They're sensitive and expensive.

392
00:38:41,990 --> 00:38:45,450
The front part of this one is cracked.

393
00:38:45,450 --> 00:38:47,400
Yes, the bridge fell.

394
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:51,020
I have only ever heard of that happening, it's the first time I actually see it.

395
00:38:51,020 --> 00:38:52,370
It happens sometimes.

396
00:38:52,370 --> 00:38:56,290
It can also fall when the instrument receives a strong impact.

397
00:38:59,630 --> 00:39:05,860
By the way... I heard you aren't joining Professor Lee Soo Kyung's chamber orchestra anymore.

398
00:39:06,620 --> 00:39:09,250
Yes, it ended up that way.

399
00:39:09,250 --> 00:39:13,090
How did you know? Rumors travel really fast.

400
00:39:14,130 --> 00:39:16,240
This field is so small.

401
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:20,990
By sitting here, I hear all kind of stories I don't even want to hear.

402
00:39:20,990 --> 00:39:23,000
Nothing interesting?

403
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:27,890
Nothing. People don't talk about other's success, you know.

404
00:39:27,890 --> 00:39:30,180
They only talk about their failures.

405
00:39:30,180 --> 00:39:35,600
What the? So you're saying all those stories of failures included my story?

406
00:39:39,620 --> 00:39:44,350
Don't be like that. Tell me. Is there nothing about someone in a worse situation than me?

407
00:39:49,830 --> 00:39:53,250
What's this? There really is?

408
00:39:55,660 --> 00:39:57,620
No, just...

409
00:39:58,750 --> 00:40:00,850
Jung Kyung.

410
00:40:02,210 --> 00:40:04,170
What about her?

411
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:07,460
She...

412
00:40:07,460 --> 00:40:12,130
She's been disowned by Professor Song Jung Hee.

413
00:40:18,270 --> 00:40:21,290
   

414
00:40:21,290 --> 00:40:25,790
I don't think I can be your accompanist. I'm sorry.

415
00:40:25,790 --> 00:40:30,170
I'm about to fail being appointed anyway, so there's no need for you to be my accompanist?

416
00:40:30,170 --> 00:40:33,970
Is that what this is?

417
00:40:33,970 --> 00:40:35,970
That's not it.

418
00:40:35,970 --> 00:40:38,380
Then why can't you do it?

419
00:40:47,620 --> 00:40:49,720
I understand.

420
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:53,450
You're done, right?

421
00:40:53,450 --> 00:40:58,720
About the money... I'll repay you.

422
00:41:01,860 --> 00:41:03,840
And...

423
00:41:06,170 --> 00:41:12,460
Let's... not see each other anymore.

424
00:41:13,900 --> 00:41:15,830
Ever again.

425
00:41:40,670 --> 00:41:44,090
   

426
00:42:10,620 --> 00:42:13,760
 If you don't have a place to practice, you can just come here.  

427
00:42:22,780 --> 00:42:26,430
I'll go now, so practice at ease.

428
00:42:26,430 --> 00:42:29,020
Am I maybe stopping you from practicing?

429
00:42:29,020 --> 00:42:31,210
I was going to go home.

430
00:42:33,250 --> 00:42:34,720
Work hard.

431
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:36,650
Thank you.

432
00:43:02,080 --> 00:43:05,430
- Hello. 
 - Hello.

433
00:43:08,090 --> 00:43:09,700
- Thank you. 
 - Thank you.

434
00:43:09,700 --> 00:43:11,760
Let's enjoy the meal.

435
00:43:11,760 --> 00:43:14,160
- Enjoy. 
 - Yes.

436
00:43:20,220 --> 00:43:21,770
It's delicious.

437
00:43:21,770 --> 00:43:24,330
Yes, it is.

438
00:43:32,290 --> 00:43:36,480
You were taken aback when I suddenly asked you to eat tteokbokki, weren't you?

439
00:43:36,480 --> 00:43:39,950
No, I also like tteokbokki.

440
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:42,230
Really?

441
00:43:42,230 --> 00:43:45,790
I like instant tteokbokki the most, actually.

442
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:48,680
I see.

443
00:43:50,070 --> 00:43:53,710
I couldn't have any since coming back to Korea, actually.

444
00:43:59,190 --> 00:44:01,160
 Welcome. 

445
00:44:01,160 --> 00:44:02,880
 Have you been well? 

446
00:44:02,880 --> 00:44:04,800
 What's the occasion? 

447
00:44:08,290 --> 00:44:10,240
 Instant tteokbokki. 

448
00:44:13,340 --> 00:44:15,040
Song Ah.

449
00:44:16,390 --> 00:44:22,100
I'm really glad that a good person like you is by Joon Young's side.

450
00:44:22,100 --> 00:44:25,270
I sincerely think so.

451
00:44:28,580 --> 00:44:33,050
Well... somehow it turned out this way.

452
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:38,890
When I came to Korea after graduating, I had many dreams.

453
00:44:40,040 --> 00:44:43,050
What were they?

454
00:44:46,060 --> 00:44:49,510
To earn a living while playing the cello I like,

455
00:44:49,510 --> 00:44:53,450
and start a family with the person I love.

456
00:44:53,450 --> 00:44:56,630
But it turned out to be quite a difficult thing to achieve.

457
00:44:58,910 --> 00:45:05,730
Until now, both for the cello and in love, I was getting back from it as much as the amount of effort I put in.

458
00:45:06,910 --> 00:45:11,030
But now it feels too unfamiliar. Everything does.

459
00:45:42,540 --> 00:45:48,220
 Until now, there were only two times when I summoned the courage to do something.  

460
00:45:48,220 --> 00:45:52,500
  - Song Ah, you're not finding a job, but majoring in something else? 
 - Yeah.  

461
00:45:52,500 --> 00:45:53,480
 Fighting for me too? 

462
00:45:53,480 --> 00:45:56,390
 You've gone mad, right. 

463
00:45:56,390 --> 00:45:57,860
 I'm not mad. 

464
00:45:57,860 --> 00:46:01,460
 You're applying to the College of Music instead of getting a job? 

465
00:46:02,550 --> 00:46:09,900
 Song Ah. Do you have a talent for the violin? 

466
00:46:12,250 --> 00:46:14,680
 For the violin...  

467
00:46:24,360 --> 00:46:27,500
 I like you, Joon Young. 

468
00:46:27,500 --> 00:46:29,460
 ... and for love.  

469
00:46:38,090 --> 00:46:40,690
 Since I love it so much... 

470
00:46:44,580 --> 00:46:49,190
 Am I... not a member? 

471
00:46:49,190 --> 00:46:53,300
 Of course not. I only gathered the talented ones here. 

472
00:46:53,300 --> 00:46:55,000
 Then even though I get hurt  

473
00:46:55,000 --> 00:46:57,670
 Song Ah. Our secretary. 

474
00:46:57,670 --> 00:47:00,150
 and hurt over and over,  

475
00:47:01,930 --> 00:47:07,650
 I thought I could continue to love.  

476
00:47:12,170 --> 00:47:14,630
 Perhaps, that might have been  

477
00:47:16,770 --> 00:47:18,800
 my... 

478
00:47:24,060 --> 00:47:27,130
 own vanity.  

479
00:47:48,690 --> 00:47:50,810
Ah, Unni?

480
00:47:52,350 --> 00:47:54,080
What is it?

481
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:58,870
I heard you sent Jung Kyung away.

482
00:47:58,870 --> 00:48:03,670
But I saw she hasn't withdrawn her application to the Professor position, yet.

483
00:48:05,000 --> 00:48:10,090
Do you think she's in the state of mind to think about that, now?

484
00:48:10,850 --> 00:48:12,770
Right...

485
00:48:12,770 --> 00:48:15,080
But...

486
00:48:18,360 --> 00:48:25,830
I do kind of think it would be nice if Jung Kyung became a Professor... now.

487
00:48:27,100 --> 00:48:28,890
What?

488
00:48:28,890 --> 00:48:34,240
I'm thinking of backing her up. Nothing says I can't, after all.

489
00:48:48,560 --> 00:48:50,230
What is it about?

490
00:48:50,230 --> 00:48:54,190
I'm sure you didn't call me just to see me.

491
00:48:55,730 --> 00:48:57,820
Uhm, perhaps...

492
00:49:00,060 --> 00:49:04,900
Would it be possible to schedule a performance or an event?

493
00:49:06,980 --> 00:49:10,100
Of course. Yes, of course.

494
00:49:10,100 --> 00:49:12,990
I'll look into it.

495
00:49:12,990 --> 00:49:15,050
- Thank you. 
 - No, well.

496
00:49:16,440 --> 00:49:22,490
Then about the payment, will something around what was expected from the event at Kyunghoo Cards work?

497
00:49:23,470 --> 00:49:29,500
Would maybe a little more be possible?

498
00:49:32,740 --> 00:49:35,660
   

499
00:49:50,990 --> 00:49:52,930
Yes?

500
00:50:00,330 --> 00:50:03,330
Song Ah. What do you need?

501
00:50:05,790 --> 00:50:08,310
Hello, Professor.

502
00:50:08,310 --> 00:50:11,150
I came to tell you something.

503
00:50:11,150 --> 00:50:13,160
Yes, go ahead. By the way,

504
00:50:13,160 --> 00:50:18,100
it's better if I wear it on the side without the pocket, right?

505
00:50:19,760 --> 00:50:22,000
How is it?

506
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:24,330
Here. Is it nice?

507
00:50:24,330 --> 00:50:29,390
Ah right! Are you scheduling with Joon Young your lessons together?

508
00:50:31,710 --> 00:50:35,410
Since you're dating him, you should adapt to his mood.

509
00:50:35,410 --> 00:50:38,490
Musicians are always sensitive and fussy.

510
00:50:38,490 --> 00:50:42,920
They aren't ordinary people, so you can't date them like you would anyone else.

511
00:50:42,920 --> 00:50:43,960
Right?

512
00:50:43,960 --> 00:50:47,540
Anyway, talk to him and bring him over here.

513
00:50:47,540 --> 00:50:52,420
I'm thinking of asking him to be a collaborator in our chamber orchestra's new year performance.

514
00:50:52,420 --> 00:50:54,420
Okay? Ah!

515
00:50:54,420 --> 00:50:56,900
What is it? What did you want to say?

516
00:51:03,420 --> 00:51:06,090
- Professor. 
 - Yes?

517
00:51:07,480 --> 00:51:13,870
I will... quit my work for the chamber orchestra.

518
00:51:22,810 --> 00:51:24,610
What?

